caption: This has to be the slowest customer service someone can ever receive. The employees are very racially bias and only prepare orders of their regular customers at a fast and speedy pace. Out of all of the Starbucks location that I patronize this has got to be the worst and most unprofessional employees location in the loop area. They aren’t that sanitary with handing of food and preparation for drinks. Avoid this location if you don’t mind waiting for your order unless you use their mobile app which does not always list the item you would like to order.
A Starbucks that I go to often, great coffee and snacks, it hits the spot.

Love this starbucks.great sitting arrangement.

One of the best Starbucks operations in town. 5 stars for great management and efficient service. Staff make an effort to get to know you and your regular preferences in drinks. You don't have to tell them twice what you want. They have lots of traffic, but the staff is very efficient. Manager (Moira) is regularly seen behind the bar actively working during rush hours. I have been going here for the past 6 month. Has been a great experience all along. Keep up the good work!

Probably the worse in the city. Unfriendly staff that do not know the meaning of fast paced. I actually saw an employee once take off their open toed, and back, sandal, and wash it off in the hand sink. Avoid this one!

There’s 6 people behind the counter and barely 10-12 people waiting for their stuff. This isn’t the first time I had to wait. Another time I ordered at the store and had to wait 30 mins almost for two coffees when there were barely 5 people.

I've never left a Starbucks this annoyed. Got there this morning when it wasn't that busy and the cashier was great! Then I ended up waiting 30 mins for my order. Normally I wouldn't mind if it were busy but it got to the point where people were coming in and leaving 5 mins later, order in hand. REALLY not ok. To top it off the barista was not very nice about it and I had to ask multiple times about my order. Got my drink and it wasn't how I had ordered it - thanks for making me feel like I was the bother dude. Not giving them my business again. 2 stars cause the cashier was nice and got my name & order right for once.

I love Starbucks, but since my office location changed, I've been extremely disappointed with the service at this location. It's a joke. Considering how busy a hub it is, you would think they would bring in competent baristas or more help. Not the case here. The waiting area right now is 30 people deep. Coffee still tastes great but waiting 15 minutes every morning to get my fix is a total buzzkill. Taking my business elsewhere next week.

Despite going to Starbucks on a daily basis as a loyal customer, I could not believe the service I received yesterday at this location after my purse was STOLEN. The manager showed zero compassion and said things get stolen at his location "every day". If that is the case this place needs full time security! If you do go to this location, keep your items very close to you as theft is clearly an issue.
